%html
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "Content-Type"}/
    :css
      div {
          width: 200px;
          height: 100px;
          background-color: yellow;
          /* Rotate div */
          -ms-transform: rotate(7deg); /* IE 9 */
          -webkit-transform: rotate(7deg); /* Chrome, Safari, Opera */
          transform: rotate(7deg);
      }
  %body
    %div Hello
    %br/
    %p
      %b Note:
      Internet Explorer 8 and earlier versions do not support the transform property.
    %p
      %b Note:
      Internet Explorer 9 supports an alternative, the -ms-transform property. Newer versions of IE support the transform property (do not need the ms prefix).
    %p
      %b Note:
      Chrome, Safari and Opera supports an alternative, the -webkit-transform property.
